Two people were killed and seven others injured in a horrific accident on the N3 at the Brickfield Road offramp just after 7pm on Monday evening. Garrith Jamieson of ALS Paramedics said upon arrival, KZN VIP Medical Paramedics carnage. “A light delivery vehicle with passengers on the back lost control on the N3 freeway before overturning multiple times and ejecting most of its passengers before coming to rest on its wheels. The driver, a male in his thirties, was found severely entrapped in his vehicle. “He had sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene. A female passenger in her twenties was also found with fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for her and she was declared deceased on the scene,” Jamieson said. He added that the deceased driver’s wife was in the car, however, it was not confirmed whether the female that died in the crash had any relations to the driver.  “I do suspect the deceased were related in some way, however, it was not confirmed,” Jamieson said. He said seven others sustained critical injuries and were stabilised on the scene by multiple Advanced Life Support Paramedics before being rushed to a nearby Durban hospital for the further treatment that they required. At this stage the events leading up to the accident are unknown however SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further.